awk : (a) Scans a file line by line
(b) Splits each input line into fields
(c) Compares input line/fields to pattern
(d) Performs action(s) on matched lines

 awk '{print $1,$4}' file.txt
 
 
 
Cut : cut command in UNIX is a command for cutting out the sections from each line of files
-d = dilimter , -c = column , -b = bytes , -f = fixed lenghth



Xargs - xargs reads items from standard input as separated by blanks and executes a command once for each argument
echo 'one two three' | xargs mkdir
ls
one two three



Find : Find command is used to search and locate the list of files
and directories based on conditions you specify for files that match the arguments
find . -name tecmint.txt



sed - substitution or for find and replace
$sed 's/unix/linux/g' test.txt - replaces the word unix with linux globally in file



